{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Swift Concurrency — introduced in Swift 5.5 — reshapes how iOS apps make asynchronous network calls. When integrating with Claude, the concurrency model does more than eliminate callback pyramids: it gives you structured lifetimes that cancel child work automatically, actors that eliminate data races by construction, and task groups that trivially fan out multiple Claude requests in parallel. This section covers the concurrency patterns that matter most for Claude-powered apps and explains how they interact at each layer of the stack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Six Key Patterns" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Six Swift concurrency patterns for Claude: Actor Isolation, Task Group, AsyncStream Bridge, MainActor ViewModel, Structured Cancellation, Continuation Bridge"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 1: Actor Isolation" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "actor" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " serialises access to its mutable state across concurrent callers. Wrapping "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "ClaudeClient" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in an actor means you can share one client across a view model without a single mutex, DispatchQueue, or lock. Concurrent calls are enqueued automatically by the Swift runtime."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "actor ClaudeClient {\n    private let session = URLSession.shared\n    private var history: [Message] = []  // protected by actor\n\n    // Callers must await — only one call executes at a time\n    func chat(prompt: String, apiKey: String) async throws -> String {\n        history.append(Message(role: \"user\", content: prompt))\n        let response = try await sendRequest(messages: history, apiKey: apiKey)\n        history.append(Message(role: \"assistant\", content: response))\n        return response\n    }\n\n    func resetHistory() {\n        history = []  // no lock needed — actor guarantees exclusivity\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Actor reentrancy:" },
              { "type": "text", "text": " A Swift actor is reentrant at suspension points (at " },
              { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
              { "type": "text", "text": "). While one call is suspended waiting for the network, another call can enter the actor. This means state you read before an " },
              { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
              { "type": "text", "text": " may differ from state you read after it. Check state again after every suspension if it matters." }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 2: Task Groups for Parallel Claude Calls" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you need multiple independent Claude responses simultaneously — summarising several documents, generating variations of a prompt, or categorising a list of items — "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withThrowingTaskGroup" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " fans out calls in parallel and collects results. All child tasks are automatically cancelled if the group throws."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "struct DocumentAnalysis {\n    let document: String\n    let summary: String\n}\n\nfunc analyseAll(documents: [String], apiKey: String) async throws -> [DocumentAnalysis] {\n    try await withThrowingTaskGroup(of: DocumentAnalysis.self) { group in\n        for document in documents {\n            group.addTask {\n                let prompt = \"Summarise in one paragraph: \\(document)\"\n                let summary = try await ClaudeClient.shared.chat(\n                    prompt: prompt,\n                    apiKey: apiKey\n                )\n                return DocumentAnalysis(document: document, summary: summary)\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Collect in completion order (not submission order)\n        var results: [DocumentAnalysis] = []\n        for try await result in group {\n            results.append(result)\n        }\n        return results\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a Claude application with multiple users or parallel agent workflows, this pattern enables you to process N items in roughly the time it takes to process one, limited only by rate limits from the API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 3: AsyncThrowingStream for SSE" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If you need to publish a Claude stream to multiple observers, or build a pipeline that transforms deltas before they reach the UI, wrap the URLSession SSE loop in an "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "AsyncThrowingStream" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Callers iterate it with "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "for try await" },
          { "type": "text", "text": " just like any other async sequence." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "func streamDeltas(\n    messages: [Message],\n    apiKey: String\n) -> AsyncThrowingStream<String, Error> {\n    AsyncThrowingStream { continuation in\n        Task {\n            do {\n                let request = try makeRequest(messages: messages, apiKey: apiKey)\n                let (bytes, _) = try await URLSession.shared.bytes(for: request)\n\n                for try await line in bytes.lines {\n                    guard line.hasPrefix(\"data: \") else { continue }\n                    let json = String(line.dropFirst(6))\n                    if json == \"[DONE]\" { break }\n\n                    let event = try JSONDecoder().decode(StreamEvent.self, from: Data(json.utf8))\n                    if event.type == \"content_block_delta\",\n                       let text = event.delta?.text {\n                        continuation.yield(text)  // push to stream\n                    }\n                }\n                continuation.finish()  // mark stream done\n            } catch {\n                continuation.finish(throwing: error)  // propagate errors\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Usage:\nfor try await delta in client.streamDeltas(messages: msgs, apiKey: key) {\n    await MainActor.run { viewModel.output += delta }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 4: @MainActor ViewModel" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Marking the ViewModel class "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "@MainActor" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " ensures all "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "@Published" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " mutations happen on the main thread, eliminating the manual "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await MainActor.run { }" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " calls inside every streaming callback. A "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Task { }" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " created inside a "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "@MainActor" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " context automatically inherits that actor and hops back to the main thread after each "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
          { "type": "text", "text": "." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@MainActor\nfinal class ChatViewModel: ObservableObject {\n    @Published var output = \"\"\n    @Published var isStreaming = false\n\n    private let client = ClaudeClient()\n    private var task: Task<Void, Never>?\n\n    func send(prompt: String, apiKey: String) {\n        task?.cancel()\n        output = \"\"\n        isStreaming = true\n\n        task = Task {\n            // This Task inherits @MainActor, so output mutations\n            // are main-thread safe without extra wrapping\n            do {\n                let stream = client.streamDeltas(\n                    messages: [.init(role: \"user\", content: prompt)],\n                    apiKey: apiKey\n                )\n                for try await delta in stream {\n                    output += delta  // safe — we're on MainActor\n                }\n            } catch is CancellationError {\n                // no-op\n            } catch {\n                output = \"Error: \\(error.localizedDescription)\"\n            }\n            isStreaming = false\n        }\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 5: Structured Cancellation" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Swift's structured concurrency model cancels child tasks automatically when their parent is cancelled or when an error propagates up. For Claude streaming this means cancelling the top-level Task also closes the URLSession connection and any in-flight processing in task groups."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Check cancellation in CPU-bound loops between Claude calls\nfunc processWithClaude(items: [String], apiKey: String) async throws -> [String] {\n    var results: [String] = []\n    for item in items {\n        try Task.checkCancellation()  // throws CancellationError if cancelled\n        let result = try await ClaudeClient.shared.chat(\n            prompt: \"Process: \\(item)\",\n            apiKey: apiKey\n        )\n        results.append(result)\n    }\n    return results\n}\n\n// In the view model — cancel on disappear\n.onDisappear {\n    viewModel.task?.cancel()\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The key distinction: "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Task.checkCancellation()" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " throws eagerly — use it between iterations. "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Task.isCancelled" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a Boolean check — use it when you need to branch without throwing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern 6: withCheckedThrowingContinuation" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If you work with an older Claude SDK or wrapper that uses completion handlers instead of async/await, bridge it into the async world with "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withCheckedThrowingContinuation" },
          { "type": "text", "text": ":" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Legacy callback-based Claude wrapper (hypothetical)\nfunc legacyClaudeChat(\n    prompt: String,\n    completion: @escaping (Result<String, Error>) -> Void\n) { /* ... */ }\n\n// Async wrapper using continuation\nfunc claudeChat(prompt: String) async throws -> String {\n    try await withCheckedThrowingContinuation { continuation in\n        legacyClaudeChat(prompt: prompt) { result in\n            continuation.resume(with: result)\n        }\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Resume exactly once:" },
              { "type": "text", "text": " A continuation must be resumed exactly once. If the callback fires multiple times (or never), you have undefined behavior. Use " },
              { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withCheckedContinuation" },
              { "type": "text", "text": " (which checks at runtime and crashes on double-resume) rather than the unchecked variant." }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Sendable Conformance" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you pass data across actor boundaries (e.g., from "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "@MainActor" },
          { "type": "text", "text": " to " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "ClaudeClient actor" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "), the types must conform to "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Sendable" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Swift 5.9+ with strict concurrency checking will warn (and in Swift 6, error) when non-Sendable types cross boundaries."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Value types (struct) are implicitly Sendable if all properties are Sendable\nstruct Message: Codable, Sendable {\n    let role: String\n    let content: String\n}\n\n// Classes need explicit conformance or @unchecked Sendable\n// (only use @unchecked when you've manually guaranteed thread safety)\nfinal class PromptCache: @unchecked Sendable {\n    private let lock = NSLock()\n    private var cache: [String: String] = [:]\n\n    func cached(for key: String) -> String? {\n        lock.lock(); defer { lock.unlock() }\n        return cache[key]\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Testing Async Claude Code with XCTest" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "XCTest supports "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "async" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " test functions directly since Xcode 13. Use a protocol to swap out the real Claude client for a mock:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "swift" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "protocol ClaudeClientProtocol {\n    func chat(prompt: String, apiKey: String) async throws -> String\n}\n\n// Production\nextension ClaudeClient: ClaudeClientProtocol {}\n\n// Mock for tests\nstruct MockClaudeClient: ClaudeClientProtocol {\n    var response: String\n    var error: Error?\n\n    func chat(prompt: String, apiKey: String) async throws -> String {\n        if let error { throw error }\n        return response\n    }\n}\n\n// Test\nfinal class ChatViewModelTests: XCTestCase {\n    @MainActor\n    func testSendUpdatesOutput() async {\n        let mock = MockClaudeClient(response: \"Hello from Claude\")\n        let vm = ChatViewModel(client: mock)\n        vm.send(prompt: \"Hi\", apiKey: \"test\")\n\n        // Give the Task a cycle to run\n        await Task.yield()\n\n        XCTAssertFalse(vm.output.isEmpty)\n    }\n\n    @MainActor\n    func testErrorSetsMessage() async {\n        let mock = MockClaudeClient(\n            response: \"\",\n            error: URLError(.timedOut)\n        )\n        let vm = ChatViewModel(client: mock)\n        vm.send(prompt: \"Hi\", apiKey: \"test\")\n        await Task.yield()\n\n        XCTAssert(vm.output.contains(\"Error\"))\n    }\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Concurrency Pattern Comparison" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Use case" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Pattern" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableHeader", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Why" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Single chat message" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await client.chat()" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Simplest; actor ensures safe shared state" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Streaming response" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "AsyncThrowingStream" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Composable; can pipe through transform stages" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "N independent prompts" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withThrowingTaskGroup" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Parallel; auto-cancels all on first error" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "SwiftUI binding" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "@MainActor" },  { "type": "text", "text": " class" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Compiler-enforced UI thread safety" }] }] }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Legacy callback SDK" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withCheckedThrowingContinuation" }] }] },
              { "type": "tableCell", "content": [{ "type": "paragraph", "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Bridge one-shot callbacks to async/await" }] }] }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Assuming actor serialisation prevents all races." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " Actor access is serialised, but actors are reentrant at " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " points. If you read state, suspend, and read state again, a different caller may have mutated it in between. Design state transitions to be complete before suspending, or re-read after every " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": "." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Creating Task { } inside init." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " A Task created in " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "init()" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " captures " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "self" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " before the object is fully initialised. Move long-lived tasks to an explicit " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "start()" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " method or a SwiftUI " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": ".task { }" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " modifier." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Not checking cancellation between iterations." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " Without " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "try Task.checkCancellation()" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " in a loop, cancellation only takes effect at the next " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "await" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " suspension — which can be delayed by many iterations of CPU work." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Using Task.detached when a structured Task suffices." },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "Task.detached" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " does NOT inherit actor context or cancellation from its parent. Use it only when you genuinely need to escape the current scope — for example, for a background refresh that should outlive the view." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }], "text": "Resuming a continuation more than once." },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " If the callback passed to " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withCheckedThrowingContinuation" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " fires twice (e.g., a retry on timeout), the second " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "continuation.resume" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " crashes with a fatal error. Wrap the continuation with a guard or " },
                  { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "nonisolated(unsafe) var resumed = false" },
                  { "type": "text", "text": " to prevent double-resume." }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Summary" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Swift Concurrency gives Claude-powered apps a clean model for every scenario: a single "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "actor" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for shared conversation state, "
          },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "code" }], "text": "withThrowingTaskGroup" },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for parallel multi-prompt workloads, "
          },
